{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3101","heading":"Definitions","label":"3101 Definitions","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/ch49","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries","Short Title, , , provided that:Pub. L. 116–323, § 1134 Stat. 5075Jan. 5, 2021“This Act [enacting this chapter] may be cited as the ‘National Landslide Preparedness Act’.”"],"amendments":["Short Title, , , provided that:Pub. L. 116–323, § 1134 Stat. 5075Jan. 5, 2021“This Act [enacting this chapter] may be cited as the ‘National Landslide Preparedness Act’.”"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":"3D","label":"1 3D","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “3D” means 3-dimensional.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":"3D elevation data","label":"2 3D elevation data","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":"In general","label":"A In general","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “3D elevation data” means 3D, high-resolution data obtained using LiDAR, IfSAR, or other methods over the United States (including territories).","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":"Inclusions","label":"B Inclusions","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “3D elevation data” includes terrestrial and bathymetric elevation data.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":"3D elevation program","label":"3 3D elevation program","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “3D Elevation Program” means the 3D Elevation Program established under .section 3104(a) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"4","heading":"IfSAR","label":"4 IfSAR","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/4","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F4","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “IfSAR” means interferometric synthetic aperture radar.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"5","heading":"Indian tribe","label":"5 Indian tribe","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/5","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F5","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Indian tribe” has the meaning given the term in .section 5304 of title 25","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"6","heading":"Lahar","label":"6 Lahar","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/6","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F6","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/6/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F6%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"often fast-moving; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/6/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/6","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F6%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a hazard in watersheds downstream of volcanic peaks.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"7","heading":"LiDAR","label":"7 LiDAR","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/7","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F7","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “LiDAR” means light detection and ranging.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"8","heading":"Secretary","label":"8 Secretary","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/8","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft43%2Fs3101%2F8","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The term “Secretary” means the Secretary of the Interior, acting through the Director of the United States Geological Survey.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"9","heading":"State","label":"9 State","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s3101/9","parentId